[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    115[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   1. **The recruitment-decision-record journal is a clinical-trial-record-class artifact accumulating multi-year per-trial and per-participant content.** ICH E6 GCP retention obligations for FDA-regulated trial records typically require retention for 15+ years (or 2 years after the last marketing application approval, whichever is longer); for unmarketed investigational products, retention can extend further. The recipe correctly elevates that "the records are retained per the institutional research-data-retention policy and per the trial's specific retention requirements" but the architecture must specify per-trial-record-class retention reconciliation across HIPAA's six-year minimum, ICH E6 GCP retention, 21 CFR Part 312 IND record retention, 21 CFR Part 812 IDE record retention, sponsor-contract retention obligations, FDORA diversity-action-plan retention obligations, state-specific medical-record retention for participants who later enroll, FDA SaMD post-market obligations where applicable, and litigation-hold obligations.
