[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    121[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   4. **The vulnerable-population sensitive-record classification is recipe-distinct.** Pediatric records (Subpart D), pregnant-women records (Subpart B), prisoner records (Subpart C), and cognitively-impaired records each have category-specific consent posture and retention regimes. The architecture must specify per-category sensitive-record handling.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    122[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    123[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   5. **The sponsor-recruitment-data-sharing posture is recipe-distinct.** Where the trial is sponsor-funded, the sponsor's recruitment-data-access-and-sharing rights are governed by the sponsor agreement; the architecture must specify per-trial sponsor-data-sharing posture distinct from institutional retention.
