[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **The bounded-conversation-surface framing earns its position.** "Unlike the longitudinal coordination assistant, the recruitment conversation is typically a single session or a small number of sessions. Unlike the chronic disease coach, the recruitment conversation has a defined endpoint (qualified-handoff to coordinator, declined-by-patient, or screen-failed-by-eligibility). Unlike the mental-health support bot, the recruitment conversation does not establish a long-term relationship; the coordinator establishes the long-term relationship if the patient enrolls." This is the recipe's clearest architectural articulation.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **The eight-structural-commitments enumeration is recipe-distinct and load-bearing.** IRB-approved-content corpus as only allowed source of trial-specific language; per-trial protocol-specific context loading and per-trial isolation; eligibility-evaluation engine with deterministic per-criterion logic and named clinical-leadership ownership; coordinator-handoff orchestration as production scope; trial-state and trial-amendment tracking; representativeness instrumentation per trial and per recruitment cohort; vulnerable-populations-aware identity model; research-data-as-distinct-record-class with research-grade retention. These are the recipe's correct architectural elevations.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **The fourteen-property "Why a Generic LLM Cannot Run a Clinical Trial Recruitment Conversationalist" enumeration is recipe-distinct and earns its position.** No theory of IRB-approved recruitment language; no theory of eligibility-criteria depth; hallucinates trial information when grounding is weak; no theory of staying within scope; no theory of assent versus consent versus surrogate-decision-maker; no theory of vulnerable populations; clinical-decision-rule arithmetic problems; no theory of trial-status state; no theory of what to do when patient is in distress; no theory of relationship to existing care team; compliance implications specific to recruitment data; no theory of representativeness monitoring; no theory of coordinator-handoff quality; no theory of trial-comparability when multiple trials are in scope.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **The thirteen-task-surface decomposition is correctly granular.** Entry from referral source; trial-specific context loading and disclosure; patient-question-handling using IRB-approved FAQ retrieval; conversational eligibility prescreen; prescreen-result delivery; coordinator-handoff orchestration; equity-and-representativeness instrumentation; sensitive-topic handling within recruitment scope; continuous emergency screening; out-of-scope routing; per-conversation audit and IRB-grade record retention. This decomposition maps cleanly to the Python companion's ten-step implementation (per the code review's mapping table).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **The "Recruitment Reality" subsection's seventeen-property enumeration is the recipe's most-distinctive contribution.** The IRB-as-active-participant, the trial-sponsor-as-also-active-participant, the recruitment-funnel-not-conversation-count metric framing, the demographic-representativeness-as-regulatory-and-scientific-obligation framing, the equity-considerations-cut-deep framing, the protocol-amendments-routine framing, the protocol-confidentiality-real framing, the coordinator-capacity-hard-constraint framing, the clinician-referral-path-structural framing, the site-specific-operations-matter framing, the decentralized-and-hybrid-trials-change-the-architecture framing, the pediatric-vulnerable-population-and-surrogate-decision-maker-scenarios-change-the-identity-model framing, the outcome-demonstration-takes-the-entire-trial-timeline framing, the existing-patient-recruitment-vendors-relationship-structural framing, and the trial-portfolios-accumulate framing are each the recipe's right register.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **The "Where the Field Has Moved" subsection's eight-update enumeration earns its position.** Decentralized-clinical-trials-have-changed-the-recruitment-surface, diversity-action-plans-increasingly-formalized, ClinicalTrials.gov-and-trial-listing-infrastructure-has-matured, tool-using-LLMs-handle-recruitment-conversations-well-when-grounded-carefully, hybrid-AI-plus-coordinator-recruitment-is-the-dominant-production-pattern, outcome-demonstration-positive-for-hybrid-models, build-vs-buy-mature-for-some-recruitment-segments, equity-and-representativeness-work-is-an-active-area-of-investment.
